// Hackathon GCP Cloud Workstations Basics - Question Bank (GIFT)

::WB01_PwdPurpose::
What does `pwd` usually show?
{
=Your current folder location
~Your GitHub username
~Your cloud billing status
~Your browser history
}

::WB02_LsPurpose::
What does `ls` help you do?
{
=See files and folders in the current location
~Start a web server
~Sign into GitHub
~Create an API key
}

::WB03_CdPurpose::
Why is `cd` important in a terminal?
{
=Many commands only work if you are in the correct folder
~It closes browser tabs
~It creates pull requests
~It uploads secrets automatically
}

::WB04_CloudWorkstationsPurpose::
In this hackathon, what is Cloud Workstations mainly used for?
{
=To provide a browser-based development environment inside GCP
~To replace the Google Cloud project selector
~To store billing invoices only
~To create YouTube playlists
}

::WB05_ReadmeUse::
A README is mainly helpful because it:
{
=Explains setup, prerequisites, and how to run the project
~Stores browser cookies
~Acts as a cloud credential
~Replaces all code files
}

::WB06_RepoMeaning::
What is a repository?
{
=A project and its stored change history
~A list of browser bookmarks
~A cloud region
~A password manager
}

::WB07_GcpConsole::
Why does the Google Cloud Console matter in this hackathon?
{
=It is where you confirm the correct account, project, services, and settings
~It replaces the workstation terminal
~It stores the quiz answers
~It is only for billing teams
}

::WB08_EnvVarPurpose::
Why are environment variables used?
{
=To provide runtime values such as configuration and secrets
~To replace file explorers
~To create browser tabs
~To format markdown files
}

::WB09_SecretHandling::
What is the best practice for API keys and tokens?
{
=Do not paste them into public places or screenshots
~Store them in the repo README
~Send them in a public chat for backup
~Rename them so they are not secret anymore
}

::WB10_CloudProject::
Why does the correct GCP project matter?
{
=Services, APIs, and permissions are usually tied to a specific project
~It changes your keyboard layout
~It decides which browser you use
~It removes the need for documentation
}
